                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-purple-900">What Are Common Signs of Stress?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-purple-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>Stress can manifest in various ways, including physical symptoms like headaches, muscle tension, fatigue, and trouble sleeping. Emotionally, it may cause irritability, mood swings, anxiety, or feeling overwhelmed, while cognitively it can lead to forgetfulness, negative thinking, and difficulty concentrating. Recognizing these signs early is key to managing stress before it becomes unmanageable.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 2 -->
        <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-purple-300">
            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-purple-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-purple-900">Is All Stress Bad for Me?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-purple-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>Not all stress is harmful—positive stress, called "eustress," can motivate you and improve performance, like when preparing for an exam or presentation. On the other hand, long-term stress, known as "distress," can negatively impact health if not managed properly, emphasizing the importance of balance and healthy coping mechanisms.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 3 -->
