            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-purple-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-purple-900">What Is the Difference Between Anxiety and Stress?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-purple-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>Stress is a response to specific challenges, such as work or personal conflicts, and usually diminishes once the stressor is resolved. Anxiety, however, is more persistent and doesn't always have an identifiable cause. Unlike stress, which can sometimes motivate you, anxiety tends to have a negative impact on daily life and often requires treatment to manage.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 4 -->
        <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-purple-300">
            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-purple-200 " onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-purple-900">When Should I Seek Professional Help for Stress?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-purple-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>Seeking professional help is important if stress persists without improvement, significantly affects your daily life, or causes severe physical symptoms like chronic headaches. Additionally, if stress results in anxiety, depression, or leads you to use unhealthy coping mechanisms like alcohol, it’s time to reach out to a mental health professional for support.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
